There would be no difference to them with one single petition or 4,000 seperately mailed/dev board submitted obvious form letter type petitions.<br>
<br>
Seeing and noting the existence of a petition, or even reading it, does not mean they are going to be any more apt to change anything.<br>
<br>
I think the druid is a great class also, I love it and I love my epic. If you want to be the best uber group needed class, then you should not be a druid. They(classes like warrior, etc) bought their position in the higher end or group game via sucking for a long time and being LFG for nine hours while we enjoyed doing whatever the heck we pleased, very easily, at level 14 plus (just using that as an example because that is sow plus our first real DOT) <br>
<br>
It is called balance. Any time you have a class in Everquest which solos WELL, giving it anymore advantages for grouping makes it solo even BETTER. In the end you have a master class which is way out of balance with the rest of them. A warrior was a good tank at level 20 and is a great tank at level 60 but in both cases its a very sucky tank out on its own without a cleric. <br>
<br>
I try to think of ways they could improve the druid class<br>
for grouping while not making us even MORE powerful while<br>
soloing OR making us TOO desireable for grouping, but they are kind of hard to think up. That might be a good direction to go in though when submitting requests to verant. One that is often mentioned is Group Healing for AOE type situations. Problem then is, Paladins have kind of found a niche in AOE groups due to being able to Group Heal while filling other rolls and a druid getting that would step on the toes of the paladin who is NOT as welcome in other regular groups and who CAN'T really solo its way out of a paper bag. Once again, you get balance problems.<br>
<br>
A swiss army knife will not be the best tool for the job, but its the best tool if you often want to do MANY jobs while only having ONE tool. That is about the best summary of all the things a druid can do that I can think of. Like the swiss army knife, this is going to come at a price and you may one day wish you had a real seperate saw, spoon or corkscrew. You must also remember that like the swiss army knife, you enjoyed the versitality for quite a long time before you came to a point where you wished you had a more specialized tool.<br>
<br>
I think we should all send verant our individual opinions via the developer's corner, I often do. <p><center><BR>
